casebody.data:
IANTHE CALHOUN v. HONORABLE W. T. HARRISON, etc. 13 So. (2nd) 14

January Term, 1943

April 16, 1943 Division B Alvan B. Rowe, for petitioner. J. Tom Watson, Attorney General, Woodrow M. Melvin, Assistant Attorney General, and' Clyde Wilson, State Attorney, for respondents. *741PER CURIAM:

Upon petition of the plaintiff to amplify and clarify the order of the court, entered 10 February 1943, and upon further consideration of the cause, it is ordered that the former order be amended by adding the words “without prejudice.”

BUFORD, C. J., BROWN, THOMAS and SEBRING, JJ„ concur.
